ALdulfe Abbot of Peterborough, succéeded Oswald in  both his Sees, viz of Yorke and Worceter, a holy and reuerend man (saith 

      〈◊〉
   ) and one that striued with his predecessor in liberality toward the monastery of Floriake. He died May 6. 1002. and was buried in Saint Maries church at Worceter.
